                <encodingDesc>
                        <p>Main text from M2 with variants from other editions as listed above. Line
                                division as per lines or hemistichs of this edition; departures of
                                structure in other editions noted in variants (V presents hemistichs
                                as separate lines, so its division only remarked on when in conflict
                                with M2). Any emendations of structure given by M2 noted in variants
                                and indicated in main text by [[supplied text]]. C and A are musical
                                editions, dependent for their text on M2 and V respectively;
                                significant departures from respective source texts indicated,
                                otherwise can be read as containing all variants listed for source
                                text.</p>
                        <p>As editions vary in treatment of archaic forms, linguistic focus etc.
                                departures from M2 text only recorded where considered significant.
                                Use of i/j/y, u/v not recorded; however use of m/n, differences in
                                word division and capitalization all included. Syllabification in
                                musical editions is indicated by "_". Variation in refrain repeats:
                                all departures from pattern of M2 are indicated; fluctuating forms
                                in any of the sources are indicated, marked by "~", under the first
                                refrain.</p>
                        <p>All variants given within the text.</p>
